{
  "texts": [
    "An RST begins by defining an outcome of concern, such as a specified reduction in supply to an end user.",
    "The RST then estimates which upstream changes in production, capacity, or trade could plausibly produce that outcome.",
    "Because these systems are layered, the analysis must account for how losses at one stage translate into constraints at others.",
    "The task is therefore to identify the configuration of upstream perturbations most likely to generate the observed downstream disruption.",
    "Ultimately, this approach reframes the analysis of supply chain resilience."
  ]
}